    <h1>Download</h1>

    <p>The Grinder 2 and The Grinder 3 can be downloaded from <a
    href="http://www.sourceforge.net/projects/grinder">SourceForge.net</a>.
    They are packaged as a <code>zip</code> format files which you
    should expand using <code>unzip</code>, <a
    href="http://www.winzip.com">WinZip</a> or similar.
    </p>

    <h2>What else do I need?</h2>

    <p>To run the Grinder:</p>

    <blockquote>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <td><a href="http://java.sun.com/j2se/">J2SE 1.3.1</a> or equivalent</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </blockquote>

    <p>and optionally:</p>

    <blockquote>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <td><a href="http://java.sun.com/products/jsse/">JSSE 1.0.2</a></td>
          <td>&#160;</td>
          <td>for SSL support</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><a href="http://jakarta.apache.org/ant/index.html">Apache Jakarta Ant 1.5.1</a></td>
          <td>&#160;</td>
          <td>to build The Grinder from source</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/junit/">JUnit 3.7</a></td>
          <td>&#160;</td>
          <td>to test The Grinder itself</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </blockquote>

   <p>Later versions of these packages should also work.</p>

</body>
</html>
